{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0c251299-db72-4c05-8181-7e9d149dec64","content":"None of my available skills cover **dump analysis** — they focus on dump *collection*, tracing, and Android tombstones.\n\nHere's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, CLI)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n   - `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n2. **Visual Studio** (Windows) — open the `.dmp` directly, click \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows, advanced) — load SOS via `.loadby sos coreclr`, then use `!pe`, `!clrstack`, `!threads`\n\n4. **`lldb` + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n   ```bash\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   plugin load /path/to/libsosplugin.so\n   sos clrstack\n   ```\n\n### Quick Start\n\nIf you have `dotnet-dump` available and can share the dump path, I can launch an interactive analysis session right here. Want me to do that?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3a124b8e-d5b7-490d-8688-22af3722cd08","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file and wants to analyze it. Let me check if any of the available skills are relevant here.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files, not .dmp files\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing dump files. \n\nSince I don't have the right tools available, I should walk the user through the manual process of analyzing their .dmp file using standard debugging tools.","outputTokens":532},"id":"407bace0-cc1d-4cef-9d1f-6c5b9437f396","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:01:09.186Z","parentId":"9f06fbaf-2c2c-46e9-9de4-aec8828ce6b9"}
